---
import Base from '../../layouts/Base.astro';
import Hero from '../../components/Hero.astro';
---

<Base
  title="The company"
  description="La Tulpa, contemporary dance and dance theatre company founded in 2023 by Manuel Monró. Inclusive creation from Seville and Barcelona."
>
  <!-- ASSET: Replace with company photo (image prop) when available -->
  <Hero title="The company" height="section" />

  <article class="section container">
    <div class="prose">
      <div class="reveal">
        <p>
          La Tulpa was born in 2023. Not from a plan, but from an encounter: Manuel Monró meeting the 16th Escena Mobile International Festival of Art and Diversity in Seville. A festival that since 2007 has opened space for inclusive arts and everything that conventional stages leave out.
        </p>
        <p>
          From that encounter came <em>Ensayo sobre nadie</em> (Essay on Nobody), the company's first piece. And from that piece, a way of working: contemporary dance and dance theatre, simple and precise movement, scenic research, a chiaroscuro aesthetic where half-light does not hide but invites you to look more slowly.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="reveal reveal-delay-1">
        <h2 class="accent-underline">The name</h2>
        <p>
          In the Tibetan tradition, a tulpa is a being that takes form through thought and will. A thought that becomes body. The image fits the company's poetics: bodies that think, thought that moves.
        </p>
        <!-- NOTE FOR MANUEL: please confirm the meaning you give to the name -->
      </div>

      <div class="reveal reveal-delay-2">
        <h2 class="accent-underline">Language</h2>
        <p>
          La Tulpa works in the territory of inclusive creation. Not as a theme, but as a form. What happens on stage is born from difference: from distinct bodies that meet, listen, transform one another. Each piece is an investigation. Each performance, an act of presence.
        </p>
        <p>
          The company moves between Barcelona and Seville. It has toured Spain, South Korea and Germany. It works in close relationship with Compañía Danza Mobile from Seville and with the international circuit of accessible dance.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </article>
</Base>
